a:3:{s:11:"notes_total";i:5;s:11:"notes_ctree";a:5:{i:0;a:32:{s:2:"id";i:85;s:5:"title";s:35:"OpenCRM extends Timeline to Assets";s:4:"href";s:63:"http://weekcrm.com/blog/all/opencrm-extends-timeline-to-assets/";s:13:"href-original";s:63:"http://weekcrm.com/blog/all/opencrm-extends-timeline-to-assets/";s:4:"time";a:2:{i:0;i:1770188400;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:13:"last-modified";a:2:{i:0;i:1770100693;i:1;a:2:{s:6:"offset";i:18000;s:6:"is_dst";b:0;}}s:4:"text";s:827:"<p>OpenCRM updated its Assets module by adding the Timeline view, bringing record history/activity tracking into asset management.</p>
<h3>What changed</h3>
<p>Assets now include a Timeline, giving teams a single place to review related activity and updates tied to an asset record.</p>
<h3>Why it matters</h3>
<p>For organizations tracking equipment, managed assets, or other items inside OpenCRM, Timeline support makes asset records easier to review over time—without jumping between modules or relying on separate notes/logs.</p>
<h3>More details</h3>
<p>OpenCRM points users to an overview of the Assets feature for a broader context on how the module is used.</p>
<p>Learn more here: <a href="https://productupdates.opencrm.co.uk/en/news/391">https://productupdates.opencrm.co.uk/en/news/391</a></p>
